{"architecture":{"frozen_components":[],"mechanism_tags":["chain-of-thought","reasoning-rationales","self-taught","reward-model-verifier","test-time-compute"],"seam_cell":"text","summary":"STaR-SQL reframes text-to-SQL generation as a reasoning-driven process. The system prompts an LLM to produce detailed step-by-step reasoning rationales for SQL queries, then fine-tunes the model on rationales leading to correct outcomes. At inference time, the model generates both reasoning steps and SQL queries. An outcome-supervised reward model (ORM) verifier is incorporated to score and select high-quality SQL predictions, scaling the inference process through test-time computation.","trained_components":["base LLM fine-tuned on reasoning rationales","outcome-supervised reward model (ORM) verifier"]},"biblio":{"authors":["Mingqian He","Yongliang Shen","Wenqi Zhang","Qiuying Peng","Jun Wang","Weiming Lü"],"citation_count":{"as_of":"2026-07-09","source":"openalex","value":3},"title":"STaR-SQL: Self-Taught Reasoner for Text-to-SQL","venue":null,"year":2025},"claims":[{"baseline":null,"claim_id":"c1","compute_reported":false,"dataset":"Spider","evidence":"claimed","evidence_ref":null,"metric":"execution accuracy","scale":null,"statement":"STaR-SQL achieves an execution accuracy of 86.6% on the Spider benchmark","type":"quantitative","unit":"percent","value":86.6},{"baseline":{"name":"few-shot baseline","value":null},"claim_id":"c2","compute_reported":false,"dataset":"Spider","evidence":"claimed","evidence_ref":null,"metric":"execution accuracy improvement","scale":null,"statement":"STaR-SQL surpasses a few-shot baseline by 31.6%","type":"quantitative","unit":"percent","value":31.6},{"baseline":{"name":"fine-tuned direct-answer baseline","value":null},"claim_id":"c3","compute_reported":false,"dataset":"Spider","evidence":"claimed","evidence_ref":null,"metric":"execution accuracy improvement","scale":null,"statement":"STaR-SQL surpasses a baseline fine-tuned to predict answers direc